13 WHEREAS, agriculture is one of Oklahoma's leading industries and
14 its associated production, processing, and marketing sectors
15 combined provide nearly 200,000 jobs and contribute more than $28
16 billion to our state's economy; and
17 WHEREAS, Oklahoma ranks fourth nationally with more than 77,000
18 farms and ranches, utilizing 32.9 million acres of Oklahoma's rich
19 land to provide food, fiber, and other necessities of life to
20 Oklahomans and people across the world; and
21 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is known as the nation's premier spot for
22 wheat production and research, ranking third for winter wheat
23 bushels harvested annually; and
